categories: Bodea Catalog,Bodea Catalog/Products,Bodea Catalog/Products/Electronic Test and Instrumentation/Hardware/FlexRIO Custom Instruments and Processing
name: Bodea PXIe-7966R FlexRIO FPGA Module
description:
The LabVIEW FPGA Module helps you develop and debug custom hardware logic that you can compile and deploy to Bodea FPGA hardware.

LabVIEW FPGA is a software add-on for LabVIEW that you can use to more efficiently and effectively design FPGA-based systems through a highly integrated development environment, IP libraries, a high-fidelity simulator, and debugging features. You can create FPGA VIs that combine direct access to I/O with user-defined LabVIEW logic to define custom hardware for applications such as digital protocol communication, hardware-in-the-loop simulation, and rapid control prototyping. Though the LabVIEW FPGA Module contains many built-in signal processing routines, you can also integrate existing hardware description language (HDL) code as well as third-party IP.
meta_description: The LabVIEW FPGA Module helps you develop and debug custom hardware logic that you can compile and deploy to Bodea FPGA hardware.

categories: Bodea Catalog,Bodea Catalog/Products/Electronic Test and Instrumentation/Hardware/FlexRIO Custom Instruments and Processing
name: SHC68-C68-D4 Shielded Single-Ended Cable-2 m
description:
Connects high-speed digital I/O, multifunction DAQ, and FlexRIO devices directly to individual header pins or other accessories.

The Digital Cable models include a variety of industry-standard front- and back-end connectors, such as 68-pin VHDCI, 68-pin D-SUB, and flying lead options. Some models can connect digital instruments with other accessories to break out cable signals for direct access. Others provide flying leads that plug directly into any 0.1 in. header connector.
meta_description: Connects high-speed digital I/O, multifunction DAQ, and FlexRIO devices directly to individual header pins or other accessories.

categories: Bodea Catalog,Bodea Catalog/Products/Electronic Test and Instrumentation/Hardware/FlexRIO Custom Instruments and Processing
name: PXIe-7911
description:
Adds FPGA-based signal processing capability to PXI systems and can stream at a high bandwidth.

PXI FlexRIO Coprocessor Modules feature high-performance FPGAs that add signal processing capability to PXI systems. These modules leverage the latest FPGAs from Xilinx, streaming technologies such as PCI Express, and Bodea Peer to Peer Streaming for high-bandwidth data communication with other modules over the backplane. When paired with another PXI device, such as a PXI Vector Signal Transceiver, PXI FlexRIO Coprocessor Modules provide the additional FPGA resources required to run complex algorithms in real-time.
meta_description: Adds FPGA-based signal processing capability to PXI systems and can stream at a high bandwidth.

name: PXIe-7912
description:
Adds FPGA-based signal processing capability to PXI systems and can stream at a high bandwidth.

PXI FlexRIO Coprocessor Modules feature high-performance FPGAs that add signal processing capability to PXI systems. These modules leverage the latest FPGAs from Xilinx, streaming technologies such as PCI Express, and Bodea Peer to Peer Streaming for high-bandwidth data communication with other modules over the backplane. When paired with another PXI device, such as a PXI Vector Signal Transceiver, PXI FlexRIO Coprocessor Modules provide the additional FPGA resources required to run complex algorithms in real-time.
meta_description: Adds FPGA-based signal processing capability to PXI systems and can stream at a high bandwidth.
